We have this setup:
Replication set with master on xx.xx.xx, slave on localhost and arbiter also on xx.xx.xx.

We start the script.
A query is done to determine the total amount to work on in our collection.
Then the script process forks 12 times, creating 12 new instances (or so I hoped) of MongoConnection
Each fork works now on 10.000 entries. 
Then the forks exit, giving back control to the master.
The master then needs to count the total number of documents from the collection that have been handled by the forks.
